x4freetext: 1. The first correction concerned elastically scattered
deuterons which emerged at angle greater than 30 degr.
This correction was negative and less than 9% in all
2.The second correction was for nuclear reactions
producing charged particles which entered detector with
energies above discriminator level for the detector.
This correction was positive and always less than 3.5%
3. Correction on false detected reaction products.
4. Correction on undetected deuterons was negative and
5. Correction due to finite target thickness and finite
beam size were estimated to be negligible.
Two thin passing scintillators and two annular
scintillators served to identify properly directed
deuterons incident on the thin, solid, circular
targets, which were approximately 1 cm in diameter.
